Availability
============

   The latest information about SINGULAR is always available from
`http://www.mathematik.uni-kl.de/~zca/Singular'.  The program SINGULAR
and the above mentioned parts are available via anonymous ftp through
the following addresses:
GMP
     (C) Free Software Foundation: `libgmp-2.0.2.tar.gz'
     `ftp://ftp.gnu.ai.mit.edu' or its mirrors

readline
     (C) Free Software Foundation: `libreadline-2.0.tar.gz'
     `ftp://ftp.gnu.ai.mit.edu' or its mirrors

MP
     (C) Gray/Kajler/Wang, Kent State University: `MP-1.1.2.tar.gz',
     `http://mcs.kent.edu/pub/MP'

Factory
     (C) Greuel/Stobbe, University of Kaiserslautern:
     `factory-1.3b.tar.gz'
     Contact <factory@mathematik.uni-kl.de> for details on Factory.

libfac
     (C)  Messollen, University of Saarbruecken: `libfac-0.3.0.tar.gz'
     Contact <michael@math.uni-sb.de> for details on libfac.

SINGULAR binaries
     `ftp://www.mathematik.uni-kl.de/pub/Math/Singular/' or via a WWW
     browser from
     `http://www.mathematik.uni-kl.de/ftp/pub/Math/Singular/'

